# TESTING & QUALITY RULES
## CORE PHILOSOPHY
Tests are executable documentation. They must be deterministic, fast, and behavior-driven.

## TESTING STRATEGY
- Follow the Testing Pyramid: heavily favor fast, isolated unit tests, supplemented by integration and E2E tests.
- Test behaviors and public interfaces, not private implementation details.
- Implement strictly isolated tests: no shared mutable state, no dependencies on run order.

## MOCKING & BOUNDARIES
- Mock all external boundaries (network, disk, database, time) in unit tests.
- Use dependency injection to make external dependencies easily mockable.
- Ensure integration tests hit real database/service instances (via containers/ephemeral environments) rather than mocks.

## COVERAGE & SCENARIOS
- Cover the happy path, edge cases, and explicit failure modes/exceptions.
- Reproduce discovered bugs as tests before fixing the underlying code.
- Treat test code with the same quality standards as production code (DRY, well-named, modular).